The paper deals with the problem of estimating missing entries in kernel matrices, which is a common problem in machine learning and data analysis. The use of a parametric model and the em algorithm are both techniques commonly used in the field of machine learning, particularly in the sub-fields of statistical learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The application of the method to bacteria clustering experiments suggests a potential connection to the sub-fields of computer vision (cs.CV) and computational biology (cs.SI), while the use of kernel matrices is also relevant to the sub-field of data structures and algorithms (cs.DS).
